 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>EMERGENCY PATCH</b></font></a> <p>There is currently an emergency patch in progress.  Estimated downtime is 2 hours, finishing at approximately 6pm PST.<P><br>
The patch message addendum has also been released.<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>EVERQUEST EXPANSION NAMED</b></font></a> <p>Yet another detail has emerged on the new EverQuest expansion in the works.  It will be entitled <b>Shadows of Luclin</b>.<P><br>
The <a href='http://everquest.station.sony.com/luclin/index.jsp'>official page</a> does nothing more at this time but confirm its name, but that will probably change as more details are released in the near future.<P><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>PATCH MESSAGE</b></font></a> <p>The patch message has been released! There is a massive amount of changes from monk weight limits, Warrior Epic weapons, food, and many many more. Be sure to check it out.<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>SWG REALM LAUNCHES</b></font></a> <p>The newest site in the Casters Realm Network has now officially launched! Check out the new <b><a href='http://swg.crgaming.com/'>Star Wars Galaxies Realm</a></b> with yours truly as the admin. Just as with EQ Casters Realm we'll bring you all the latest news on Verant's newest project. Check it out!<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>PATCH DAY!</b></font></a> <p>The patch day has arrived! There are several options you can do here at Casters Realm to fight off those withdrawals while the servers are down.<br>
<p>First you can stop by our forums and talk with other EverQuest fans about plenty of topics.<br>
<br>You can access the forums from the link to the left or <b><a href='http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi'>here</a></b>.<br>
<p>Second you can drop into our IRC Chat and chat with others waiting for the servers to come back up.<br>
<br>You can access the IRC chat at irc.castersrealm.com in #everquest, or you can use our handy client <b><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/chat'>here</a></b>.<br>
<p><br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>RELIGIONS, FACTIONS, AND YOU!</b></font></a> <p>Continuing a popular discussion about religions and factions, Alan replied to a few comments and questions. He explained why changing relegions would be difficult to implement, the reason why there are no diety specific spell lines, and a quick explanation on Velious faction systems.<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>ALL YOU EVER WANTED TO KNOW (ALMOST)</b></font></a> <p>Alan replied to multiple comments regarding the "In Development" section of the EverQuest page on todays forums. Some of his answers included what is planned for the NPC return feature, the downfalls of the "In Development" section, and the definition of the "bi-weekly" patch schedule.<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>ABSOR'S GUIDE TO ECONOMICS</b></font></a> <p>In yet another post in the Server Economies section, Absor replied to a few suggestions and questions from players. This time Absor explained inflation in EQ and also stated how an all no-drop economy would not work.<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>MORE ON HIDE/SNEAK</b></font></a> <p>Continuing the discussion on hiding and sneaking, a ranger queried Alan as to why only rogues could use those skills at the same time. Alan replied, stating that as before, this is an inherrant advantage for the rogue class.<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>FORAGING UP A SOLUTION</b></font></a> <p>Absor took a moment on today's forums to clear up a common misconception regarding the foraging enhancements. He explained that you will <u>only</u> forage food or water when you have the hungry or thirsty message.<br>
 <p> </p><br>
